text: the Indonesian police chief says four of
the perpetrators died in the attack two
of them after detonating suicide bombs
the other two died in an exchange of
gunfire with the security forces the
attack took place outside a coffee shop
on one of the main roads running through
central jakarta number of explosions
were heard in the area and gunfire
continued for more than an hour the
police had been on high alert over the
new year after getting warnings of a
possible large-scale operation by groups
supporting the so-called Islamic state
the authorities in the world's most
populous Muslim country have been
relatively successful in curbing violent
militant activities after the Bali
bombings of 2002 which killed more than
200 mainly Western tourists and were
carried out by a regional affiliate of
al Qaeda the last big attack took place
more than six years ago on to Jakarta
hotels jonathan haidt BBC news
